  },
  {
    question: "What does chat capture from HVAC visitors?",
    answer: "The AI records the HVAC requirement category (heat pump, air conditioning, ventilation, chiller, or maintenance), the property or building type and size, the current system manufacturer and age, the heating or cooling concern, the energy source, any grant awareness, and the visitor's contact details for your follow-up."
  },
  {
    question: "Does chat slow my HVAC contractor website?",
    answer: "MCS certification badges, heat pump installation photography, manufacturer partner logos, and Trustpilot review feeds load at their full speed before the chat widget initialises. The lightweight component loads asynchronously entirely after existing page content renders. No measurable impact on page speed or search ranking."
  },
  {
    question: "Is website chat a separate charge?",
    answer: `Website chat comes bundled with phone answering at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month — no additional fee. HVAC contractors gain dual coverage: weekday phone calls from facilities managers tendering VRF replacements and developers specifying MVHR systems, combined with evening and weekend chats from homeowners whose oil bills have prompted serious heat pump research.`
